My last post was a few days ago.. and I welcomed Class Less to the site.  In my opinion she seems to be an articulate and intelligent person.  But my opinion is wavering.  She has a tendency to reach conclusions based upon false premise.  From her posts I perceive that she doesn't know shit about VA Hospitals or military medicine in general.<br>
I feel that she.. like Spatz.. may get some sort of buzz from jerking our chain(s).  Also, like Sputtering Spatz... she won't settle for our acceptance of her.  She wants to be one of us.. a Combat Veteran!  She views the VVA's offer of an associate membership as an insult.<br>
I believe that this person has had a problem with feeling accepted all her life.  Perhaps she (and only she knows)has done some rather weird things to gain acceptance.. like go to Vietnam!  Jane Fonda went to North Vietnam to gain recognition (A perceived form of acceptance.)  And.. she did gain acceptance in some circles.<br>
I don't know of one Red Cross worker who was called a Baby Killer... or died trying to save a brother on the battlefield.<br>
I don't appreciate some person comming here to negate the ills perpetrated then and now against Vietnam  Veterans ...defending the VA.. and trying to sell me on what a great guy Barry Puke Spatz is!  Especially someone seeking to be something that they are Not!  I had my fill of that kind of bullshit from the old heroic bedpan pusher we grew to know and hate.<br>
For some reason I just don't appreciate counterfiet people!<br>
I respect your right to be on this site.  I appreciate any effort that you may have made to comfort my wounded brothers.. but don't try your two-bit counseling on traumatized men who have forgotten more than you will ever know about pain.  How many times in Vietnam did you have your friend's gray matter splattered across your face?  How many leeches did you pull off your ass?  How much muddy water did you drink?  How many times were you wounded?  How many times were you told that you would never walk again?  How many service personnel did you have to deal with that had been dead for three days?  You are not a Vietnam Veteran per se, you are a pseudo veteran... just like the Phillipino truck drivers that made more money that I did.. and never left the base.  If YOU want to kiss the asses of those who violated and still violate us... then help yourself!  But don't come here spouting your great achievement and contributions as a G.I. Jane... a product of Hollywood!  You should find enough acceptance in the fact that veterans appreciate and respect you for what you did.. and that's all!  Nothing more... nothing less!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
P.S.  The Vietnam Veterans of America won't even let Wharf Rat Spatz be an associate member.
